author: COMSOL
description: In this tutorial a headphone is simulated in a typical measurement setup. As headphones are closely coupled to the ear, it is not representative to measure their sensitivity in an acoustic free-field in the classical setup used for loudspeakers. The measurement requires the use of artificial heads and ears to accurately represent the usage conditions. This model shows the coupling of a circumaural headphone to a generic artificial ear.
